'''''Red Shirts''''' (Italian:'''''Camicie rosse''''') is a 1952 French-Italian [[historical film|historical]] drama film directed by [[Goffredo Alessandrini]] and [[Francesco Rosi]] and starring [[Anna Magnani]], [[Raf Vallone]] and [[Alain Cuny]]. The title refers to the historical [[Redshirts (Italy)|Redshirts]]. It is also known as '''''Anita Garibaldi'''''. The film portrays the life of [[Anita Garibaldi]] (1821â€“1849), the wife of [[Italian unification]] leader [[Giuseppe Garibaldi]].<ref>Moliterno p.273</ref>

